Prompt: A magical nighttime scene featuring a tiny glowing fairy as the central figure, sitting gracefully on a blooming lilac flower. She wears a delicate dress made from flower petals, and her translucent butterfly wings shimmer gently in the moonlight. Two smaller glowing fairies hover in the background, their soft light casting a warm glow on the surrounding lilac blossoms. The setting is bathed in soft moonlight, with a bokeh background of dark purples and blues, emphasizing the dreamy, ethereal mood. The fairies themselves are the primary light source, glowing with a gentle bioluminescence that highlights their delicate features and illuminates the flowers around them. The style is fantasy illustration with fine detail, a soft painterly texture, and rich, cool nighttime tones.
In the style of a cinematic fantasy illustration style that fuses the luminous elegance of *Sky Doll* with the warmth and charm of expressive Western cartoon sensibilities.** Characters are drawn with soft, natural yet stylized proportions—rounded, friendly facial features subtly elongated for grace and emotional resonance. Eyes are large, luminous, and almond-shaped with clear gaze direction and expressive arched brows. Faces feature softly sculpted contours, subtle blush, and airbrushed lips that give expressions depth and clarity.
**Linework is smooth, clean, and slightly varied in thickness**, adding graceful definition without harshness. Shading combines cel-style softness with layered airbrushed gradients, dewy skin highlights, and subtle cinematic rim lighting. Surfaces—especially skin, hair, and fabric—are digitally polished and clean, avoiding grain or painterly texture.
**Lighting is balanced and dramatic yet gentle**, blending ambient glow with selective highlights that enhance mood without overpowering the scene. Backgrounds are softly blurred or abstracted, incorporating dreamy elements like light particles, mist, or sparkles to create a storybook or magical atmosphere.

external.description: विवेक अग्निहोत्री की बहुप्रतीक्षित फिल्म द बंगाल फाइल्स अब सिनेमाघरों में दस्तक देने को तैयार है — इसकी रिलीज़ डेट तय हो चुकी है: 5 सितंबर 2025 । यह फिल्म ‘द फाइल्स’ ट्रिलॉजी की तीसरी कड़ी है, जिसमें पहले ‘द कश्मीर फाइल्स’ और ‘द ताशकंद फाइल्स’ पहले ही रिलीज हो चुके हैं। इस फिल्म में 1946 की बंगाल की घटित डायरेक्ट एक्शन डे साम्प्रदायिक हिंसा को एक काल्पनिक वर्तमान CBI जांच से जोड़कर प्रस्तुत किया गया है। राजनीतिक विरोध और थिएटरों में रोक फिल्म की रिलीज से पहले ही विवाद उठ खड़ा हुआ है — विशेषकर पश्चिम बंगाल में। निर्देशक अग्निहोत्री का आरोप है कि राज्य सरकार और पुलिस की धमकीमयी कार्रवाई के चलते कई थिएटर मालिक इसे नहीं दिखाना चाहते। उन्होंने इसको “गैर-लागू और असंवैधानिक” बताया और कानूनी कार्रवाई की तैयारी का संकेत दिया है। निर्माता पल्लवी जोशी ने राष्ट्रपति से इस ‘अनौपचारिक प्रतिबंध’ से रक्षा की अपील की है ।

external.description:
AWS Elemental MediaConvert now integrates with Time-Addressable Media Store (TAMS), enabling customers to temporally reference and extract media asset segments. This capability allows MediaConvert customers to work more efficiently meet quick turn around deadlines. With TAMS integration, customers can extract highlights from live events for near real-time social media publishing, repurpose archived broadcast content into fresh programming or documentaries, and streamline media operations by connecting directly to existing broadcast infrastructure and content management systems.
 
 This integration is designed for customers who operate their own TAMS servers—MediaConvert does not host or manage a TAMS instance. By leveraging your own TAMS deployment, MediaConvert can ingest time-based media segments on demand and use them as inputs in your encoding workflows. Whether you’re modernizing a legacy archive, building automation around editorial workflows, or enabling UGC teams to clip and publish with precision, the combination of MediaConvert and TAMS provides a powerful foundation for flexible, high-performance media processing at scale.
 
 Please visit the https://www.bbc.co.uk/opensource/projects/project/tams and https://docs.aws.amazon.com/mediaconvert/latest/ug/tams-input.html for more information on this new feature.
external.title: MediaConvert now supports Time-Addressable Media Store (TAMS)
